subject: p19028690
Findings: Low lung volumes are present. The heart size is mildly enlarged. Mediastinal and hilar contours are unchanged with similar fullness of the superior mediastinum attributable to mediastinal fat. There is no pulmonary vascular congestion. No focal consolidation, pleural effusion or pneumothorax is identified. There are multilevel degenerative changes in the thoracic spine.
Impression: Low lung volumes. Otherwise no acute cardiopulmonary process.
